Articles.Content:
I was visiting Huntsville to visit some family and friends, and I took the opportunity to try out my skills with my Nikon D50 at the Space and Rocket Center. I'm not exactly the best photographer in the world, but I think I got some nice shots of the space center.

Here's the link to the Google Photos album:

[https://goo.gl/photos/z7J5ubqsZJgUcmEv7](https://goo.gl/photos/z7J5ubqsZJgUcmEv7)
Great shots... thanks for sharing them! ![:cool:](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif)

> 
> Great shots... thanks for sharing them! ![:cool:](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif)

Thank you!

I've been to the Rocket Center, too. Nice place. The rockets are pretty cool, too. I've seen the Saturn V completely shade the Saturn IB from the sun...

I'm fairly disgruntled at them mixing up Triton for Titan, though...
